<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,613,1283]" box="[199,1285,613,640]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis box="[199,305,613,639]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[319,438,613,639]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[265,1373,338,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-46@3.[191,1397,237,1944]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1A–E. Male of Zavrelimyia (Paramerina) falcata sp. n. A, Terminal flagellomere; B, wing; C, foretibia, mid tibia, and hind tibia from left to right; D Abdomen; E, hypopygium, dorsal view. Scale: A, 10 μm; B, 500 μm; C–D, 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644850/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Figure 1D</figureCitation>
). Abdominal segments banded. T IX with 5 posterior setae in irregular row.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,613,1283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis box="[199,342,650,675]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[357,472,649,675]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[265,1373,338,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-46@3.[191,1397,237,1944]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1A–E. Male of Zavrelimyia (Paramerina) falcata sp. n. A, Terminal flagellomere; B, wing; C, foretibia, mid tibia, and hind tibia from left to right; D Abdomen; E, hypopygium, dorsal view. Scale: A, 10 μm; B, 500 μm; C–D, 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644850/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Figure 1E</figureCitation>
). Anal point small, conical. Gonocoxite bulbous, 107–120 (110) µm long, 65–67 (65) µm wide, 1.69 times as long as broad; inner border of basal 1/3 with dense field of short setae. Gonostylus robust, 75–97 (76) µm long, 0.67 times as long as gonocoxite with megaseta sickle-shaped, 9–10 (9) µm long. Phallapodeme 104–107 (106) µm long extending occupying 1.04 of gonocoxite; sternapodeme 51–53 (53) µm long. HR 1.41–1.50 (1.44); HV 2.90–3.10 (3.02).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="369" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,613,1283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,828,854]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Remarks.</emphasis>
The adult male is similar to that of Indian species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hazra, Saha, Mazumdar and Chaudhuri, 2011)" baseAuthorityName="Hazra, Saha, Mazumdar and Chaudhuri" baseAuthorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Zavrelimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clara" subGenus="Paramerina">
<emphasis box="[869,1003,828,854]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Zavrelimyia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1018,1153,828,853]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Paramerina</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1168,1227,828,854]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">clara</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hazra, N. &amp; Saha, G. &amp; Mazumdar, A. &amp; Chaudhuri, P. K." pageId="4" pageNumber="369" pagination="330 - 339" refId="ref13158" refString="Hazra, N., Saha, G. K, Mazumdar, A. &amp; Chaudhuri, P. K. (2011) Records of chironomids of the tribe Pentaneurini (Diptera: Chironomidae) in the Eastern Himalayas of India. Annales de la Societ entomologique de France, 47 (3 - 4), 330 - 339. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2011.10697724" type="journal article" year="2011">Hazra, Saha, Mazumdar and Chaudhuri, 2011</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having the similar characters of abdominal punctation, LR 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1175,1180,882,896]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">I</subScript>
and CR. The new species has higher AR, and HV than 
<emphasis box="[525,541,900,925]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Z</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hazra, Saha, Mazumdar and Chaudhuri" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[555,664,899,926]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Zavrelimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clara" subGenus="Paramerina">
(
<emphasis box="[564,581,900,925]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">P</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[605,664,899,925]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">clara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The distribution of setae in posterior border of TIX is also different. The new species appears alike to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker, 1856)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[534,1083,935,962]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Zavrelimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divisa" subGenus="Paramerina">
<emphasis box="[534,668,935,961]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Zavrelimyia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[686,821,936,961]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Paramerina</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[839,906,935,961]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">divisa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[921,1074,935,962]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" pagination="21 - 30" refId="ref14874" refString="Walker, F. (1856) Insecta Britannica. Diptera. Volume 3. Reeve &amp; Benham, London, xxiv + 352 pp. pls 21 - 30." type="book chapter" year="1856">Walker, 1856</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Johannsen, 1932)" baseAuthorityName="Johannsen" baseAuthorityYear="1932" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Zavrelimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolosa" subGenus="Paramerina">
<emphasis box="[1140,1274,935,961]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Zavrelimyia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1292,1427,936,961]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Paramerina</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,226,971,997]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">dolosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Johannsen, O. A." box="[241,432,971,997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" pagination="493 - 507" refId="ref13231" refString="Johannsen, O. A. (1932) Tanypodinae from the Malayan subregion of the Dutch East Indies. Archi v fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement, 9, 493 - 507." type="journal article" year="1932">Johannsen, 1932</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
having the similar character of costa, which is not produced but disagrees in abdominal colouration. It is close to another Indian species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chaudhuri and Debnath, 1985)" baseAuthorityName="Chaudhuri and Debnath" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Zavrelimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quininficia" subGenus="Paramerina">
<emphasis box="[711,845,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Zavrelimyia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[864,999,1007,1032]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Paramerina</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1017,1138,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">quininficia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chaudhuri, P. K. &amp; Debnath, R. K." pageId="4" pageNumber="369" pagination="167 - 171" refId="ref12415" refString="Chaudhuri, P. K. &amp; Debnath, R. K. (1985) Two new species of Paramerina Fittkau from India (Diptera: Chironomidae). In: Fittkau, E. J. (Ed.), Beitrage zur Systematik der Chironomidae, Diptera. Spixiana, Supplement, 11, 167 - 171." type="journal article" year="1985">Chaudhuri and Debnath, 1985</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in AR but has higher values of CR and HR. Shape of the gonocoxite and gonostylus also differ between the two species. The robust gonostylus of 
<emphasis box="[585,608,1079,1104]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Z.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Mondal &amp; Mukherjee &amp; Hazra, 2022" authorityName="Mondal &amp; Mukherjee &amp; Hazra" authorityYear="2022" box="[615,744,1078,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Zavrelimyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcata" status="sp.n." subGenus="Paramerina">
(
<emphasis box="[624,641,1079,1104]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">P</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[666,744,1078,1104]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[751,804,1078,1104]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is unique among the species of the subgenus. The combination of characters stated in the diagnosis justifies it to be a new member of the genus. The submitted sequences have shown 93.16 % similarity with 
<accessionNumber box="[563,682,1149,1175]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/LC462314" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">
LC 
<quantity box="[598,682,1149,1175]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.17427756" pageId="4" pageNumber="369" unit="in" value="462314.0">462314</quantity>
</accessionNumber>
in GenBank of NCBI (
<figureCitation box="[943,1042,1149,1175]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1945,1969]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,1319,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-504@4.[172,1414,1307,1921]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. The tree showing genetic relationship following Neighbor-Joining method based on the COX1 gene sequences of Zavrelimyia (Paramerina) falcata sp. n. and reference sequences of tanypod midges from GenBank. Scale: 0.020 substitutions per nucleotide position." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6644852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6644852/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Figure 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="369" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,613,1283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,535,1185,1211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">Distribution and bionomics.</emphasis>
So far, the species has been found only in the 
<typeStatus box="[1068,1116,1186,1212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="369">type</typeStatus>
locality. The imagines were collected from meadow grasslands in Kalimpong, using a light trap. The altitude is 1247 meters above mean sea level. The temperature ranges from 23°C to 28°C at the beginning of August.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
